'''"Koovy"''' was a slang adjective unique to the [[Squibbian]] dialect of [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]] used by the [[Squib/Legends|Squibs]] of [[Skor II]].

It was likely an amalgamation of ''"cool"'' and ''"groovy"'', but its use was more ubiquitous, similarly to the Basic term ''"good"''. However, it also implied extreme reverence and adoration toward the object or idea being modified.

The Squib [[King/Legends|King]] [[Ebareebaveebeedee]] declared that the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] were "koovy" during the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] crisis, and would later confer the same honor upon [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]] after the Master led the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] defense of Skor II during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

